This paper discusses a problem in machine learning related to choosing a learner's hypothesis space, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a model for automatically learning bias, which falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model is applied to related learning tasks, which could involve natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), or neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
